  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA301-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu cēṭpaṭuttup piriviṉkaṇ “aṉpiṉ iyaṟkaiyiṉ taku vakaiyatōr āṟṟāmaiyiṉāṉ” eṉṟu tōḻi taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu. [ET: iḵtu “aṉpiṉ iyalpiṉāl taruvatōr āṟṟāmaiyiṉāṉ” eṉṟu tōḻi taṉṉuḷḷē yāy maṟappu arumai colli cēṭpaṭuttatu.]</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante said to herself, during the separation when she was keeping [HIM] at a distance: “He is of an unability to bear it that is of a kind befitting to the nature of [his] love”.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA301">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>nīṇmalaik kalitta peruṅkōṟ kuṟiñci</l>
<l>nāṇmalar puraiyu mēṉip peruñcuṉai</l>
<l>malarpiṇait taṉṉa māyitaḻ maḻaikkaṇ</l>
<l>mayilō raṉṉa cāyaṟ centārk</l>
<l>kiḷiyō raṉṉa kiḷavip paṇaittōṭ </l>
<l>pāvai yaṉṉa vaṉappiṉa ḷivaḷeṉakkāmar neñcamoṭu palapā rāṭṭi</l>
<l>yāymaṟap paṟiyā maṭantai</l>
<l>tēmaṟap paṟiyāk kamaḻkūn talaḷē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>[This] girl whom mother never<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">maṟappu aṟiyā</term>: there is a type of construction with <term xml:lang="ta">aṟi</term> where the semantic significance retreats. The point is that the mother never leaves of thinking of the girl, the point in sentences where HE "does not know of coming" is that he does not come at all. Is this to be termed an idiom? Is it a kind of auxiliary construction?</note>forgets,</l>
<l rend="indent">praising [her] in many [words] with a desirous heart:</l>
<l rend="indent2">“a body as the day blossom</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the large-stemmed Kuṟiñci swollen on the long mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent2">rain eyes with dark petals like linked blossoms</l>
<l rend="indent2">from the big mountain-pool, grace just like a peacock’s,</l>
<l rend="indent2">words just like a parrot’s with red neck-stripe, bamboo shoulders</l>
<l rend="indent4">– she [is as] pretty as an image.”</l>
<l>she has fragrant tresses never without [the scent of] honey.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
